American music superstar, Beyonce, has lent her support to the ongoing End SARS protests in Nigeria. The singer took to her verified Instagram account to announce to her 155 million followers that she “has been working on partnerships with youth organisations”. The mother of three further stressed that there has to be an end to the Special Anti-Robbery Squad. Beyonce wrote, “I am heartbroken to see the senseless brutality taking place in Nigeria. There has to be an end to SARS. We have been working on partnerships with youth organisations to support those protesting for change. “We are collaborating with coalitions to provide emergency healthcare, food, and shelter. To our Nigerian sisters and brothers, we stand with you. Please visit Beyonce.com for a list of organizations to show your support.”